  "suspected_trap": "Broad realistic ruleset spanning all three rule varieties (control/watch/syscall) and both byte constants (900 watch / 1200 syscall). A cost impl must NOT flat-rate it. The execve is auid-narrowed (MEDIUM, not unrestricted HIGH); mount/time are LOW despite being syscall rules (a 'any syscall = HIGH' impl over-warns, f3 3.5). The -e 2 is control (NEGATIVE)."
